ass extermination of the Armenian People in the Ottoman Empire\" and declares April 24 as a Victims Remembrance Day.<ref name=\"standartnews.com\">{{cite news |title = Bulgaria's Parliament recognizes the armenian genocide |url = http://www.standartnews.com/english/read/bulgarias_parliament_recognizes_the_armenian_genocide-8151.html |accessdate = April 24, 2015 |agency = STANDART |date = April 24, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title = Bulgaria ambassador to Turkey summoned to MFA due to Armenian Genocide issue |url = http://news.am/eng/news/264348.html |accessdate = April 28, 2015 |agency = NEWS.AM |date = April 28, 2015 }}</ref><ref name=\"bta.bg\">{{cite news |title = Parliament Passes Resolution on Armenians' Mass Extermination in Ottoman Empire in 1915\u20131922 Period |url = http://www.bta.bg/en/c/DF/id/1065011 |accessdate = April 24, 2015 |agency = BNA |date = April 24, 2015 }}</ref>\n\nRegarding the usage of \"mass extermination\" the Bulgarian Prime Minister [[Boyko Borisov]] has specified the following:\n\"I said it very clearly: this is the Bulgarian word or the Bulgarian words, or the Bulgarian idiom for 'genocide.'\" <ref name=\"bta.bg\" />\n|-\n| {{flag|Canada}}\n| 1996, 2002, 2004,<ref>[http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/canadian-parliament-recognizes-armenian-genocide-1.509866 Canadian Parliament recognizes Armenian genocide]. [[CBC News]], 2004.</ref> 2006<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.armenian-genocide.org/Affirmation.359/current_category.1/affirmation_detail.html|title=Stephen Harper, Prime Minister of Canada|website=www.armenian-genocide.org}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Chile}}\n| 2007, 2015<ref>[http://www.camara.cl/prensa/noticias_detalle.aspx?prmid=125704 C\u00e1mara solidariza con naci\u00f3n armenia y condena genocidio]. Camara de Diputados, Chile. April 14, 2015.</ref><ref>[http://www.panorama.am/en/politics/2015/04/15/chile-parliament-genocide/ Chilean parliament once again condemns Armenian Genocide and expresses solidarity with Armenian people]. Panorama, 2015.</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Cyprus}}\n| 1975, 1982, 1990\n| The first country to raise the issue to the [[United Nations General Assembly]]. Denial of the genocide is criminalized in Cyprus.<ref>{{cite news |title = Cyprus criminalizes denial of 1915 Armenian genocide by Turks |url = https://www.reuters.com/article/2015/04/02/us-cyprus-armenia-turkey-idUKKBN0MT0YS20150402 |agency = Reuters |date = April 2, 2015 }}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Czech Republic}}\n| 2017<ref>{{cite news|title=Sn\u011bmovna poprv\u00e9 uznala genocidu Arm\u00e9n\u016f z obdob\u00ed prvn\u00ed sv\u011btov\u00e9 v\u00e1lky. Zeman ud\u00e1losti ozna\u010dil za zv\u011brstva|url=http://domaci.ihned.cz/c1-65708320-snemovna-poprve-uznala-genocidu-armenu-z-obdobi-prvni-svetove-valky-zeman-udalosti-oznacil-za-zverstva|agency=Ihned|date=25 April 2017|language=Czech}}</ref>\n|On April 14, 2015, Czech Committee on Foreign Affairs of the [[Chamber of Deputies of the Czech Republic|Chamber of Deputies]] passed a resolution on the occasion of the Armenian Genocide Centenary.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.armradio.am/en/2015/04/14/czech-parliament-panel-adopts-resolution-on-armenian-genocide-centennial |title=Czech Parliament panel adopts Resolution on Armenian Genocide centennial |publisher=Armradio.am}}</ref> On April 25, 2017 [[Parliament of the Czech Republic|Czech Parliament]] approved a resolution condemning the Armenian Genocide.<ref>{{cite news|title=Czech Republic Parliament Recognizes Armenian Genocide|url=https://horizonweekly.ca/en/czech-republic-parliament-recognizes-armenian-genocide/|publisher=Horizon|date=25 April 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|France}}\n| 1998, 2001<ref name=auron>{{cite book |last1 = Auron |first1 = Yair |title = The Banality of Denial |date = 2003 |publisher = Transaction Publishers |isbn = 1-4128-1784-6 |page = 102 |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=lQDIz5nZv0gC }}</ref>\n|The French Senate adopted a bill on October 14, 2016 that made the denial of the Armenian Genocide a crime. The bill was introduced by the French Government and passed by the French National Assembly in July, and stipulates a penalty of a year in prison or a 45,000 Euro fine.<ref name=france>{{cite news |last1 = |first1 = |title = French Senate adopts bill criminializing Armenian Genocide denial |url = https://armenpress.am/eng/news/863835/french-senate-adopts-bill-criminalizing-armenian-genocide-denial.html |agency = Armenpress |date = 14 October 2016}}</ref> On February 5, 2019, French President [[Emmanuel Macron]] declared April 24 as Armenian Genocide commemoration day in [[France]].<ref name=\"News.am\">{{cite news|url=https://news.am/eng/news/494731.html|title=Macron declares April 24 Armenian Genocide commemoration day in France|publisher=News.am}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Germany}}\n| 2005, 2016<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.dw.com/en/german-bundestag-passes-resolution-calling-ottoman-era-armenian-killings-genocide/a-19299936 |title = Bundestag passes Armenia 'genocide' resolution unanimously, Turkey recalls ambassador |author = Deutsche Welle |date = |work = dw.com |accessdate = June 2, 2016 |author-link = Deutsche Welle }}</ref>\n|Resolution passed first reading in April 2015. On June 2, 2016, the [[German Bundestag]] almost unanimously (with one vote against and one abstention) passed a resolution qualifying the Ottoman-era Armenian killings 'genocide'.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/03/world/europe/armenian-genocide-germany-turkey.html|title=German Parliament Recognizes Armenian Genocide, Angering Turkey|website=The New York Times|date=2 June 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Greece}}\n| 1996\n| Denial of the genocide is criminalized. Punishable by up to 3 years in prison and a fine not to exceed \u20ac30,000, per 2014 act.<ref>[http://jurist.org/paperchase/2014/09/greece-parliament-ratifies-bill-criminalizing-armenian-genocide-denial.php Greece parliament ratifies bill criminalizing Armenian genocide denial]. Jurist, September 10, 2014.</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Italy}}\n| 2000, 2019<ref name=auron /><ref name=guardian>{{cite news |last1 = Pascal |first1 = Julia |title = A people killed twice |url = https://www.theguardian.com/theguardian/2001/jan/27/weekend7.weekend2 |agency = The Guardian |date = January 26, 2001 }}</ref>\n| Denial of genocides is criminalized. It stipulates 3-year imprisonment and a  fine.<ref>{{cite news |title = Italy Senate moves to outlaw Holocaust denial |url = http://www.thelocal.it/20150211/italy-senate-moves-to-outlaw-holocaust-denial |agency = Local.it |date = February 11, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title = Italy Senate moves to outlaw Holocaust and genocides denial |url = http://armenpress.am/eng/news/793803/italy-senate-moves-to-outlaw-holocaust-and-genocides-denial.html |agency = Armenpress |date = February 12, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = http://arminfo.am/index.cfm?objectid=02D06760-B2B3-11E4-89190EB7C0D21663 |title = Arminfo: Senate of Italy adopts a bill criminalizing denial of Holocaust and other genocides |publisher = Arminfo.am |date =  |accessdate = April 23, 2015 }}</ref> On April 10, 2019, the [[Italian Chamber of Deputies]] adopted an initiative calling on the Italian government to recognize the Armenian Genocide and give the issue an international dimension.<ref name=\"https\">{{cite news|url=https://news.am/eng/news/506477.html|title=Italian Chamber of Deputies calls on government to recognize Armenian Genocide|publisher=News.am}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{flag|Libya}}(?)<ref>The country is divaded by a Civil war and the eastern-based interim administration is not recognized by the [[UN]].</ref>\n| 2019\n| The eastern-based interim administration's Council of Ministers has adopted a proposal from Abdelhady Alhweij, its foreign minister, to recognise the Armenian Genocide. Libya is the third Arab state to recognize the genocide, the other two being Lebanon and Syria.<ref>{{cite news |title = INTERIM GOVERNMENT RECOGNISES ARMENIAN GENOCIDE |url = https://almarsad.co/en/2019/04/18/interim-government-recognises-armenian-genocide |agency = Almarsad |date = April 18, 2019 }}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Lithuania}}\n| 2005<ref>[http://www.rferl.org/content/article/1063936.html Lithuanian Parliament Recognizes Armenian Genocide]. [[RFERL]], December 16, 2005.</ref>\n| On December 16, 2005 the Lithuanian Parliament, or Seimas, approved a resolution recognizing the Armenian Genocide.\n|-\n| {{flag|Lebanon}}\n| 1997, 2000<ref>{{cite web |url =https://www.cilicia.com/armo10i_lebanon.html|title = Lebanon Recognizes the Armenian Genocide|publisher = Cilicia |date = May 11, 2000}}</ref>\n| On May 11, 2000 the Lebanese Parliament unanimously approved a resolution calling for the commemoration of the 82nd anniversary of the Armenian Genocide perpetrated by the Ottoman Turkish government at the beginning of the century. The resolution, presented by the parliament executive, calls on all Lebanese citizens to unite with the Armenian people on April 24 in commemorating the atrocities of 1915-1923.\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Luxembourg}}\n| 2015<ref>[http://www.chd.lu/wps/wcm/connect/05f0996b-af3a-433d-8124-5243510cf957/R%C3%A9solution+g%C3%A9nocide.pdf?MOD=AJPERES&CACHEID=05f0996b-af3a-433d-8124-5243510cf957 Luxembourg, Chambre des Deputes, Resolution], May 6, 2015.</ref>\n|The [[Chamber of Deputies (Luxembourg)|Chamber of Deputies]] unanimously adopted a resolution on the recognition of the genocide of Armenian people.<ref>[http://www.chd.lu/wps/portal/public/!ut/p/b1/rZFPi8IwFMQ_0ZKXNJr22Nh_qU3cNo3aXqTiIrbVKojSfPrtwsLCwuJl35we_GbmMKhG1Yxi5lGHeWiL6kvzOB2b-2m4NP3XX893AQnWhaAEYpZTIGmYMqOV4wbzCagmgLiuLmJfhp5nOAhYYB3mnIAgr_wbVPHvEPjjfHgVUk0A-wHcjLtAlO9rlggHghkq0RboTrfjVdjOFq3NrWwjJW2FwZpRdswo0-HyHimVmSc2WGqgVpXGyu66VIfs_bAuDPd5-0j62-_COBMMSAQrvsQ5QIz_vTBF9bEf9tMimwVSyXD-QOe6z8a3ZtL--QlTBbL5/dl4/d5/L2dBISEvZ0FBIS9nQSEh/ A la Une, Luxembourg, Chambre des Deputes], May 6, 2015.</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Netherlands}}\n| 2004, 2015,<ref>[http://eu.greekreporter.com/2015/04/11/dutch-parliament-recognizes-greek-assyrian-and-armenian-genocide/ Dutch Parliament Recognizes Greek, Assyrian and Armenian Genocide]. Greek Reporter, April 11, 2015.</ref><ref>[http://www.aina.org/news/20150410044601.htm Dutch Parliament Recognizes Assyrian, Greek and Armenian Genocide]. AINA, April 10, 2015.</ref> 2018<ref>[https://nltimes.nl/2018/02/16/dutch-parliament-recognizes-armenian-genocide-minister-attend-commemoration Dutch Parliament Recognizes Armenian Genocide; Minister to Attend Commemoration], ''NL Times''</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.tweedekamer.nl/kamerstukken/detail?id=2018Z03272&did=2018D06536 |title = Motie van het lid Voordewind c.s. over erkennen van de Armeense genocide |publisher = [[House of Representatives of the Netherlands|Tweede Kamer der Staten General]] |date = February 22, 2018}}</ref>\n| The Dutch government will send a Minister or State Secretary to Armenia to attend [[Armenian Genocide Remembrance Day]] every five years, starting in 2018.<ref>[https://www.ad.nl/binnenland/kamer-erkent-voor-het-eerst-zonder-reserve-armeense-genocide~ad6ae7bc/ Kamer erkent voor het eerst zonder reserve Armeense genocide (in Dutch)],\n''Algemeen Dagblad''</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Paraguay}}\n| 2015\n| The [[Senate of Paraguay|Chamber of Senators]] in Paraguay unanimously adopted the resolution.<ref>{{cite news |title = Paraguay's Senate Recognizes Armenian Genocide |url = http://asbarez.com/141178/paraguays-senate-recognizes-armenian-genocide/ |agency = Asbarez |date = October 29, 2015 }}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Poland}}\n| 2005<ref>{{cite web |url = http://asbarez.com/52079/polands-parliament-adopts-armenian-genocide-legislation |title = Poland's Parliament Adopts Armenian Genocide Legislation |publisher = Asbarez.com |date = April 20, 2005}}</ref>\n| The ''[[Sejm]]'' of the Republic of Poland (lower house of the Polish parliament) unanimously passed a bill recognizing the Armenian Genocide on April 19, 2005.\n|-\n| {{flag|Portugal}}\n| 2019<ref>{{cite web |url =https://massispost.com/2019/04/portugals-parliament-recognizes-the-armenian-genocide/|title = Portugal's Parliament Recognizes the Armenian Genocide|publisher = MassisPost |date = April 26, 2019}}</ref>\n| On April 26, 2019, the Parliament of Portugal voted for the recognition of the Armenian Genocide perpetrated by the Ottoman Empire, with a Vote of Regret N.\u00ba 819/XIII.\n|-\n| {{flag|Russia}}\n| 1995, 2005, 2015<ref>{{cite news |title = Naryshkin: Russia's Duma recognized Armenian Genocide 21 years ago |url = https://news.am/eng/news/330869.html |agency = News.am |date = June 6, 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title = Russian State Duma adopts statement on Genocide Centennial |url = https://www.armenianow.com/genocide/62831/armenia_russia_state_duma_statement |agency = Armenianow |date = April 24, 2015 }}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Slovakia}}\n| 2004<ref>{{cite news |title = SLOVAKIA IS THE 16TH COUNTRY TO RECOGNIZE ARMENIAN GENOCIDE |url = http://panarmenian.net/eng/details/42233 |agency = Panarmenian.net |date = December 2, 2004 }}</ref>\n| Denial of the genocide is criminalized. Punishable by up to 5 years in prison, per 2011 act.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://news.am/eng/news/83038.html |title = Denial of Armenian Genocide punished in Slovakia |publisher = News.am |date = November 23, 2011 }}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Sweden}}\n| 2010<ref>[https://www.loc.gov/lawweb/servlet/lloc_news?disp3_l205401871_text Sweden: Parliament Approves Resolution on Armenian Genocide]. [[Library of Congress]], March 16, 2010.</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Switzerland}}\n| 2003<ref>{{cite news |title = Parliament recognises Armenian genocide |url = https://www.swissinfo.ch/eng/parliament-recognises-armenian-genocide/3679682 |agency = Swissinfo |date = December 17, 2003 }}</ref>\n| Denial of the genocide is criminalized.\n{{See also|Perin\u00e7ek v. Switzerland}}\n|-\n| {{flag|Syria}}\n| 2015, 2020<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.horizonweekly.ca/news/details/66204 |title = Syria recognizes the Armenian Genocide committed by the Ottoman Empire, Parliament Speaker says - \u0540\u0578\u0580\u056b\u0566\u0578\u0576 \u0577\u0561\u0562\u0561\u0569\u0561\u0569\u0565\u0580\u0569 - Horizon Weekly |publisher = Horizonweekly.ca |date = April 22, 2015 |accessdate = April 23, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url = http://asbarez.com/118921/syrian-president-finally-recognizes-the-armenian-genocide/ |title = Syrian President Finally Recognizes the Armenian Genocide |newspaper = Asbarez |date = January 28, 2014 |accessdate = October 5, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.panarmenian.net/eng/news/277901/Syrian_Parliament_unanimously_recognizes_Armenian_Genocide |title = Syrian Parliament unanimously recognizes Armenian Genocide |publisher = Panarmenian.net |date = February 13, 2020 |accessdate = February 13, 2020 }}</ref>\n| On February 13, 2020 the [[Syrian Parliament]] unanimously adopted a resolution recognizing and condemning the Armenian Genocide.\n|-\n| {{flag|United States}}\n| 2019<ref>{{cite news |title = U.S. House Votes Overwhelmingly to Lock in Armenian Genocide Recognition, Rejecting Turkey's Denial of This Crime |url = https://anca.org/press-release/u-s-house-votes-overwhelmingly-to-lock-in-armenian-genocide-recognition-rejecting-turkeys-denial-of-this-crime/ |agency = anca.org |date = October 29, 2019 }}</ref><ref name=\"USSenate\">{{cite web|url=https://eu.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2019/12/12/senate-senate-recognizes-arrecognizes-armenian-genocide-over-objections-trump-and-turkish-government/4410046002/|title=Senate recognizes Armenian genocide over objections of Trump and Turkish government|date=12 December 2019|website=USA Today}}</ref>\n| The [[United States Congress]] officially recognizes the Armenian Genocide. The [[United States House of Representatives|House of Representatives]] affirmed the United States record on the Armenian Genocide with House Resolution 296 on October 29, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-50229787?ocid=socialflow_twitter|title=US House votes to recognise Armenian genocide|website=BBC|date=29 October 2019}}</ref> The [[United States Senate|Senate]] unanimously recognized the genocide with Senate Resolution 150 on December 12, 2019.<ref name=\"USSenate\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.congress.gov/bill/116th-congress/senate-resolution/150|title=S.Res.150 - 116th Congress (2019-2020): A resolution expressing the sense of the Senate that it is the policy of the United States to commemorate the Armenian Genocide through official recognition and remembrance.|last=Menendez|first=Robert|date=2019-04-09|website=www.congress.gov|access-date=2019-12-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{flag|Uruguay}}\n| 1965, 2004<ref>{{cite news |title = URUGUAY RECOGNIZES THE ARMENIAN GENOCIDE |url = https://milwaukeearmenians.com/2015/04/17/uruguay-recognizes-the-armenian-genocide |agency = Milwaukeearmenians.com |date = April 17, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.armenian-genocide.org/Affirmation.166/current_category.7/affirmation_detail.html |title = Law No. 13.326: Day of Remembrance for the Armenian Martyrs |author = Parliament of Uruguay |date = April 20, 1965 |publisher = [[Armenian National Institute]] |accessdate = April 24, 2015 |author-link = Parliament of Uruguay }}</ref>\n| The first country to recognize the events as genocide.\n|-\n| {{flag|Holy See}}\n| 2000, 2015<ref>{{cite news |title = Pope Francis' acknowledgement of the Armenian Genocide |url = https://www.globalcitizen.org/fr/content/pope-franciss-acknowledgement-of-the-armenian-geno |agency = Globalcitizen |date = April 24, 2015 }}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| {{flag|Venezuela}}\n| 2005<ref>{{cite news |title = Venezuelan Parliament Adopts Armenian Genocide Resolution |url = http://asbarez.com/52447/venezuelan-parliament-adopts-armenian-genocide-resolution |publisher = Asbarez.com |date = July 20, 2005 }}</ref>\n| On July 14, 2005, the Parliament of Venezuela adopted a resolution that recognizes the Armenian Genocide.\n|}\n\n=== States, regions, provinces, municipalities and parliamentary committees ===\nRecognition of the Armenian Genocide also includes:\n\n;Australia \nParliaments of 2 Australian states recognize the Armenian Genocide:\n* {{flag|New South Wales}}: In 2007 the Parliament of the State of [[New South Wales]] passed a motion condemning the genocide and called on the Australian Federal Government to do the same.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parliament.nsw.gov.au/prod/parlment/hansart.nsf/V3Key/LA19970417004 |title=Armenian Genocide Commemoration |work=nsw.gov.au |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120119075550/http://www.parliament.nsw.gov.au/prod/parlment/hansart.nsf/V3Key/LA19970417004 |archivedate=January 19, 2012 }}</ref>\n* {{flag|South Australia}}: In March 2009 the Parliament of South Australia passed a similar motion to that passed in New South Wales in 2007.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://anc.org.au/news.php?item.140 |title = blanked  |author =  |date =  |work = anc.org.au |accessdate = June 2, 2016 }}</ref>\n\nAdditionally, the [[City of Ryde]] has adopted a unanimous motion dedicated to the centenary of the Armenian Genocide at its Council Meeting on April 14, 2015. The motion further calls on the Government of Australia to recognize and condemn all genocides.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://armenpress.am/eng/news/802039/city-of-ryde-recognizes-armenian-genocide.html |title = City of Ryde recognizes Armenian Genocide  |publisher = Armenpress.am |date =  |accessdate = April 23, 2015 }}</ref> The [[City of Willoughby]] passed a motion recognizing the Armenian Genocide on May 11, 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://news.am/eng/news/266255.html |title = Willoughby City Council in Australia recognizes Armenian Genocide |publisher = News.am |date =  |accessdate = May 11, 2015 }}</ref>\n\n;Belgium\n* {{flag|Flanders}}: The Parliament of Flanders adopted a resolution recognizing the Armenian Genocide and called on Turkey to come to terms with its past.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.mfa.am/en/press-releases/item/2015/04/22/flemish_parliament/ |title = Parliament of Flanders adopted resolution recognizing Armenian Genocide \u2013 Press Releases \u2013 Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Armenia |work = mfa.am |accessdate = June 2, 2016 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304084340/http://www.mfa.am/en/press-releases/item/2015/04/22/flemish_parliament/ |archive-date = March 4, 2016 |url-status = dead }}</ref>\n\n;Brazil\nParliaments of 4 Brazilian states recognize the Armenian Genocide:\n* {{flag|Cear\u00e1}}: In 2006, The Legislative Council of State of Cear\u00e1, Brazil, unanimously passed a bill which recognizes April 24 as the Day of the Armenian People. The Armenian Genocide victims will be hence commemorated on this day.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.panarmenian.net/eng/world/news/18799 |title = Ceara State of Brazil Recognized Armenian Genocide |date = July 17, 2006 |work = Panarmenian.net }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Paran\u00e1}}: In 2013, Parliament of Brazilian state of Paran\u00e1 adopted a bill recognizing the Armenian Genocide in the Ottoman Empire.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://news.am/eng/news/146659.html |title = Brazil's state of Parana recognizes Armenian Genocide |date = March 29, 2013 |work = News.am }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Rio de Janeiro}}: The State of Rio de Janeiro in Brazil recognized the Armenian Genocide on July 24, 2015 with a law, setting April 24 as \"Day of recognition and memory of the victims of the Armenian Genocide\".<ref>{{cite web |url = http://armeniangenocide100.org/en/rio-de-janeiro-state-recognizes-armenian-genocide-2 |title = State of Rio de Janeiro recognizes Armenian Genocide |date = July 25, 2015 |work = Armeniangenocide100.org |access-date = December 11, 2015 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151223163036/http://armeniangenocide100.org/en/rio-de-janeiro-state-recognizes-armenian-genocide-2/ |archive-date = December 23, 2015 |url-status = dead |df = mdy-all }}</ref>\n* {{flag|S\u00e3o Paulo}}: The [[Legislative Assembly of S\u00e3o Paulo|Legislative Assembly]] of the largest Brazilian state \u2013 S\u00e3o Paulo \u2013 passed a law recognizing April 24 \"a Commemoration Day of the 1.5 million victims of the Armenian Genocide in 1915\" in 2003.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.panarmenian.net/eng/world/news/797 |title = San-paulo brazilian state recognized armenian genocide in ottoman turkey in 1915 |date = April 30, 2003 |work = Panarmenian.net }}</ref>\n\n;Bulgaria \n* {{flag|Bulgaria}}: 5 provinces (''oblasts'') have recognized the Armenian Genocide \u2013 first in 2008 was the [[Plovdiv Province]] followed by the provinces of [[Burgas Province|Burgas]], [[Ruse Province|Ruse]], [[Stara Zagora Province|Stara Zagora]], [[Pazardzhik Province|Pazardzhik]].\n\n;Canada\n* {{flag|British Columbia}}: The [[Legislative Assembly of British Columbia]] recognized The Armenian Genocide.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://asbarez.com/53483/the-legislative-assembly-of-british-columbia-recognizes-the-armenian-genocide |title = The Legislative Assembly of British Columbia Recognizes The Armenian Genocide |work = asbarez.com |accessdate = June 2, 2016 }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Ontario}}: The [[Legislative Assembly of Ontario]] unanimously adopted a resolution recognizing the Armenian Genocide in 1980.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.armenian-genocide.org/Affirmation.123/current_category.17/affirmation_detail.html |title = Legislature of Ontario, Canada |work = armenian-genocide.org |accessdate = December 11, 2016 }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Quebec}}: Quebec was the first Province in Canada to recognize the Armenian Genocide in 1980.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www2.publicationsduquebec.gouv.qc.ca/dynamicSearch/telecharge.php?type=2&file=/J_0_2/J0_2_A.html |title = An Act to proclaim Armenian Genocide Memorial Day |work = gouv.qc.ca |accessdate = June 2, 2016 }}</ref>\nAdditionally, the City of [[Montreal]] and the City of [[Toronto]] recognized the Armenian Genocide.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://anccanada.org/thousands-of-armenian-canadians-expected-to-attend-commemorations-across-canada-to-mark-the-98th-anniversary-of-the-armenian-genocide |title = Thousands of Armenian-Canadians Expected to Attend Commemorations Across Canada to Mark the 98th Anniversary of the Armenian Genocide |accessdate = December 11, 2016 |work = anccanada.org }}</ref>\n\n;Egypt\n* {{flag|Egypt}}: In February 2019, the President of Egypt [[Abdel Fattah el-Sisi]] addressed his recognition of the Armenian Genocide during the 2019 [[Munich Security Conference]]<ref name=\"egypttoday.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.egypttoday.com/Article/2/64896/Egypt-implicitly-recognizes-Armenian-Genocide|title=Egypt implicitly recognizes Armenian Genocide|website=EgyptToday}}</ref> and had urged for complete recognition of the genocide by Egypt.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://asbarez.com/177807/egypt-president-makes-first-step-in-recognizing-armenian-genocide-says-anc-of-egypt/|title=Egypt President Takes 'First Step' in Recognizing Armenian Genocide, Says ANC of Egypt|date=February 19, 2019|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n;France\n* {{flag|Corsica}}: On April 14, 2015, the [[Corsican Assembly]] adopted a resolution recognizing the Armenian Genocide.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://armenpress.am/eng/news/801696/corsican-assembly-demands-armenian-genocide-recognition-from-turkey.html |title=Corsican Assembly demands Armenian Genocide recognition from Turkey|publisher=Armenpress.am}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Armenian Genocide Remembrance Day in Tehran, Iran 2017-04-24 08.jpg|thumb|[[Armenian Genocide Remembrance Day]] in [[Saint Sarkis Cathedral, Tehran]], 2017 (center: Archbishop [[Sepuh Sargsyan]])]]\n;Iran \n* {{flag|Iran}}: The [[Tehran]] regional government recognized the Armenian Genocide.{{citation needed|date=April 2015}} Unofficially, the [[Islamic Republic of Iran]] has repeatedly recognized the Armenian Genocide.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://titre1.ir/fa/news/11260/%D8%AC%D9%85%D9%87%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%86%D8%B3%D9%84-%DA%A9%D8%B4%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%86%D9%87-%D8%B1%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%AA-%D8%B4%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AE%D8%AA%D9%87-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA- |title = \u062c\u0645\u0647\u0648\u0631\u064a \u0627\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645\u064a \u0627\u064a\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u0646\u0633\u0644 \u06a9\u0634\u064a \u0627\u0631\u0627\u0645\u0646\u0647 \u0631\u0627 \u0628\u0647 \u0631\u0633\u0645\u064a\u062a \u0634\u0646\u0627\u062e\u062a\u0647 \u0627\u0633\u062a ! |work = \u062a\u06cc\u062a\u0631 1 |accessdate = April 24, 2016 }}</ref>\n\n;Israel \n* {{flag|Israel}}: On August 1, 2016, the [[Knesset]]'s [[Knesset Committee on Education, Culture and Sports|Education, Culture and Sports Committee]] announced its recognition of the Armenian Genocide and urged the Israeli government to formally acknowledge the 1915 mass slaughter of 1.5 million Armenians as such.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.timesofisrael.com/knesset-education-committee-recognizes-armenian-genocide|title=Knesset Education Committee recognizes Armenian Genocide|publisher=Timeofisrael.com}}</ref>\n\n;Italy \nParliaments of 9 Italian regions recognize the Armenian Genocide:\n* {{flag|Abruzzo}}: The Italian region of Abruzzo on October 27, 2015 passed a bill to recognize the Armenian Genocide.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://armeniangenocide100.org/en/italian-abruzzo-region-passes-resolution-on-genocide-recognition |title = Italian Abruzzo region passes resolution on Genocide recognition |date = October 29, 2015 |work = Armeniangenocide100.org |access-date = December 11, 2015 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151223191432/http://armeniangenocide100.org/en/italian-abruzzo-region-passes-resolution-on-genocide-recognition/ |archive-date = December 23, 2015 |url-status = dead |df = mdy-all }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Basilicata}}: The Regional Council of Basilicata, Italy, unanimously recognized the Armenian Genocide on September 27, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://consiglio.basilicata.it/consiglioinforma/detail.jsp?otype=1120&id=3372944&value=consiglioInforma#.V-wn7SOLToA |title = Genocidio popolo armeno, approvata mozione Pace |date = September 27, 2016 |work = Consiglio.basilicata.it }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Emilia-Romagna}}: The Emilia-Romagna region of Italy adopted on July 28, 2016 a resolution recognizing the Armenian Genocide.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://en.hayernaysor.am/%D5%AB%D5%BF%D5%A1%D5%AC%D5%AB%D5%A1%D5%B5%D5%AB-%D5%A7%D5%B4%D5%AB%D5%AC%D5%AB%D5%A1-%D5%BC%D5%B8%D5%B4%D5%A1%D5%B6%D5%AB%D5%A1-%D5%B6%D5%A1%D5%B0%D5%A1%D5%B6%D5%A3%D5%A8-%D5%B3%D5%A1%D5%B6%D5%A1-2 |title = Italy's Emilia-Romagna region recognizes the Armenian Genocide |date = August 3, 2016 |work = En.Hayernaysor.am |access-date = August 3, 2016 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160918022432/http://en.hayernaysor.am/%D5%AB%D5%BF%D5%A1%D5%AC%D5%AB%D5%A1%D5%B5%D5%AB-%D5%A7%D5%B4%D5%AB%D5%AC%D5%AB%D5%A1-%D5%BC%D5%B8%D5%B4%D5%A1%D5%B6%D5%AB%D5%A1-%D5%B6%D5%A1%D5%B0%D5%A1%D5%B6%D5%A3%D5%A8-%D5%B3%D5%A1%D5%B6%D5%A1-2/ |archive-date = September 18, 2016 |url-status = dead }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Lazio}}: The Regional Council of Lazio in Italy unanimously adopted a motion on recognition of the Armenian Genocide on March 18, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.panorama.am/en/news/2019/03/19/Lazio-Armenian-Genocide/2087799|title = Italy's Lazio recognizes Armenian Genocide|date = March 18, 2019 |work = panorama.am }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Lombardy}}: The Regional Council of Lombardy in Italy unanimously adopted a motion on recognition and commemoration of the Armenian Genocide on April 14, 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.consiglio.regione.lombardia.it/web/lombardiaquotidiano/archivio-articoli/-/asset_publisher/RQ2f/content/genocidio-armeno-il-consiglio-chiede-all-unanimita-la-commemorazione/maximized;jsessionid=535DBD2DA0CFF04D22A5B909BEDF15DD |title = Genocidio armeno, il Consiglio chiede all'unanimit\u00e0 la commemorazione |date = August 3, 2016 |work = consiglio.regione.lombardia.it |access-date = August 3, 2016 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170411035542/http://www.consiglio.regione.lombardia.it/web/lombardiaquotidiano/archivio-articoli/-/asset_publisher/RQ2f/content/genocidio-armeno-il-consiglio-chiede-all-unanimita-la-commemorazione/maximized;jsessionid=535DBD2DA0CFF04D22A5B909BEDF15DD |archive-date = April 11, 2017 |url-status = dead }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Marche}}: The Regional Council of Marche, Italy, unanimously recognized the Armenian Genocide on October 6, 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.armradio.am/en/2015/10/12/italian-region-of-marche-recognizes-the-armenian-genocide |title = Italian region of Marche recognizes the Armenian Genocide |date = October 12, 2015 |work = Armradio.am }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Piedmont}}: On March 31, 2015 the Regional Council of Piedmont in Italy adopted a motion on recognition and commemoration of the Armenian Genocide.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.consiglioregionale.piemonte.it/mzodgint/jsp/AttoSelezionato.jsp?ATTO=100253 |title = Ordine del Giorno n. 253, Cenrenario del Genocidio del Popolo Armeno |date = August 3, 2015 |work = Consiglioregionale.piemonte.it }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Sicily}}: The Sicilian Parliament in Italy unanimously recognized the Armenian Genocide on April 20, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.slaq.am/eng/news/1093506 |title = Sicilian Parliament unanimously recognizes the Armenian Genocide |date = April 21, 2016 |work = Slaq.am }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Tuscany}}: On March 25, 2015 the Italian region of Tuscany passed a resolution on recognition of the Armenian Genocide.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://en.hayernaysor.am/\u056b\u057f\u0561\u056c\u056b\u0561\u0575\u056b-\u057f\u0578\u057d\u056f\u0561\u0576\u0561\u0575\u056b-\u0576\u0561\u0570\u0561\u0576\u0563\u0568-\u0573\u0561\u0576\u0561\u0579\u0565\u056c-\u0567-2 |title = Italy's Tuscany Region recognizes the Armenian Genocide |date = March 26, 2015 |work = Hayernaysor.am |access-date = October 3, 2019 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20161025215547/http://en.hayernaysor.am/%D5%AB%D5%BF%D5%A1%D5%AC%D5%AB%D5%A1%D5%B5%D5%AB-%D5%BF%D5%B8%D5%BD%D5%AF%D5%A1%D5%B6%D5%A1%D5%B5%D5%AB-%D5%B6%D5%A1%D5%B0%D5%A1%D5%B6%D5%A3%D5%A8-%D5%B3%D5%A1%D5%B6%D5%A1%D5%B9%D5%A5%D5%AC-%D5%A7-2/ |archive-date = October 25, 2016 |url-status = dead }}</ref>\n\nAdditionally, almost 100 cities throughout Italy have recognized the Armenian Genocide, including [[Rome]], [[Milan]], [[Turin]], [[Venice]], [[Padua]], [[Florence]], [[Genoa]], [[Livorno]], [[Taranto]], [[Trieste]], [[Ancona]], [[Perugia]], [[Reggio Emilia]] and [[Parma]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.comunitaarmena.it/il-genocidio-armeno/italia-ricorda |title = Riconoscimenti del genocidio in Italia |date = October 1, 2016 |work = Comunitaarmena.it }}</ref>\n\n;Mexico\n*{{flag|Michoac\u00e1n}}: The Mexican state of Michoac\u00e1n adopted a statement recognizing and condemning the 1915 Armenian Genocide on May 7, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url = https://armenpress.am/eng/news/974534.html |title = Congress of Mexican state of Michoac\u00e1n adopts statement recognizing and condemning Armenian Genocide |work = armenpress.am |accessdate = May 13, 2019 }}</ref>\n\n;Netherlands\n* {{flag|Overijssel}}: The Dutch province of Overijssel adopted a motion recognizing the Armenian Genocide.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://news.am/eng/news/217525.html |title = Parliament of Dutch province of Overijssel recognizes Armenian Genocide |work = news.am |accessdate = June 2, 2016 }}</ref>\n\n;Spain \nParliaments of 5 Spanish regions recognize the Armenian Genocide:\n* {{flag|Aragon}}<ref>{{cite news |title = Parliament of Aragon in Spain Recognizes Armenian Genocide |url = http://asbarez.com/142387/parliament-of-aragon-in-spain-recognizes-armenian-genocide/ |newspaper = Asbarez |date = December 2, 2015 }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Balearic Islands}}<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.panorama.am/en/politics/2010/12/17/spain/ |title = Balearic Islands Parliament recognises the Armenian Genocide |publisher = Panorama.am }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Basque Country}}<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.panarmenian.net/eng/world/news/22156/ |title = Basque Parliament recognises Armenian Genocide |publisher = Panarmenian.net |accessdate = June 2, 2016 }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Catalonia}}<ref name=\"Catalonia\">{{cite web|author=Mher Margaryan |url=http://www.armradio.am/news/?part=pol&id=16947 |title=Catalonia Parliament recognises the Armenian Genocide |publisher=Armradio.am |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100314045703/http://www.armradio.am/news/?part=pol&id=16947 |archivedate=March 14, 2010 }}</ref>\n* {{flag|Navarre}}<ref>{{cite news |title = Parliament of Navarre Recognizes Armenian Genocide |url = http://asbarez.com/124412/parliament-of-navarre-recognizes-armenian-genocide/ |newspaper = Asbarez |date = June 24, 2014 }}</ref>\n\nAdditionally, 35 Spanish cities within 8 regions have recognized the Armenian Genocide: \n* {{flag|Andalusia}}: [[La Roda de Andaluc\u00eda]],<ref>{{cite web |url = https://armenpress.am/eng/news/842430/two-cities-in-spain-recognize-the-armenian-genocide.html |title = Two cities in Spain recognize the Armenian Genocide |publisher = Armenpress.am |accessdate = June 2, 2016 }}</ref> [[Puente Genil]],<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.armradio.am/en/2016/04/06/two-spanish-cities-recognize-the-armenian-genocide |title = Two Spanish cities recognize the Armenian Genocide |publisher = Armradio.am |accessdate = June 2, 2016 }}</ref> [[Benalm\u00e1dena]],<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.panorama.am/en/news/2016/08/12/Benalm%C3%A1dena-officially-recognized-and-condemned-Armenian-Genocide/1626665 |title = Spanish city of Benalm\u00e1dena officially recognized and condemned Armenian Genocide |publisher = Panorama.am |accessdate = August 13, 2016 }}</ref> [[Marbella]],<ref>{{ci